# PROJECT_CONTEXT.md

# Family Expense Management Application

## Project Overview

A mobile-first Family Expense Management Application built using:

* React 19
* Vite
* Tailwind CSS
* Supabase
* React Router DOM
* Context API

The application is designed for a small family group (maximum 10 users) where one Owner manages finances and permissions while other users can track expenses and create shopping requests.

The application must be mobile-first and desktop responsive.

---

# Business Requirements

The application contains two primary modules:

1. Expense Management
2. Want To Buy

After login, users see these two options and select one to continue.

Month selection is the primary navigation mechanism throughout the application.

---

# User Types

## Owner

Full system access.

Owner can:

* View all expenses
* View all spending
* Add budgets
* Add money distributions
* Manage users
* Grant permissions
* View notifications
* Customize themes
* View activity logs
* Manage Want To Buy items

Owner automatically receives all permissions.

---

## Regular User

Default user type.

Can:

* Create expenses
* Edit own expenses
* View own expenses
* Create Want To Buy items
* Edit own Want To Buy items
* View shared Want To Buy list

Has no elevated permissions.

---

## Authorized User

Regular user with individually assigned permissions.

Permissions are granted by Owner.

Authorized users can receive any combination of:

* add_budget
* view_total_spending
* add_money
* view_transactions
* view_notifications
* manage_users
* manage_want_to_buy
* customize_theme

---

# Permission System

Permissions are managed individually.

Owner Workflow:

Owner
-> Settings
-> Users
-> Select User
-> Permission Toggles

Permissions:

* add_budget
* view_total_spending
* add_money
* view_transactions
* view_notifications
* manage_users
* manage_want_to_buy
* customize_theme

Database Tables:

* permission_definitions
* member_permission_grants
* role_default_permissions

Owner receives all permissions automatically.

---

# Application Flow

Login
-> Dashboard
-> Select Module

Option A:
Expense Management

Option B:
Want To Buy

---

# Expense Management Flow

Expense Management
-> Select Month
-> Expense List
-> Add / Edit Expense

Expense Fields:

* Title
* Amount
* Description
* Category
* Date
* Month

Each expense:

* Has edit option
* Has audit history
* Generates activity logs
* Creates notifications when updated

Users:

* See own expenses

Owner:

* Sees all family expenses

Users with view_transactions permission:

* Can view expense transactions

---

# Expense Update History

Requirement:

When a user edits an expense:

Old Value
-> New Value
-> Store History
-> Notify Owner

Database:

expense_updates

Stores:

* old_data
* new_data
* updated_by_user_id

---

# Want To Buy Flow

Want To Buy
-> Select Month
-> Item List

Each item contains:

* Item Name
* Quantity
* Completed Checkbox
* Edit
* Delete

Example:

Soap | Qty 5
Milk | Qty 2
Rice | Qty 1

All family members can view list.

Owner can manage all items.

Users can edit their own items.

---

# Budget Management

Owner can create monthly budgets.

Authorized users with add_budget permission can:

* Create budgets
* Update budgets

Everyone can view budgets.

Database:

monthly_budgets

Linked to:

months

---

# Month-Based Architecture

The application is month-centric.

Database Table:

months

Example:

* June 2026
* July 2026
* August 2026

Referenced by:

* expenses
* monthly_budgets
* want_to_buy_items

Month selection occurs before viewing module data.

---

# Money Distribution

Owner can distribute money.

Workflow:

Owner
-> Select User
-> Enter Amount
-> Enter Purpose
-> Save

Database:

* money_sources
* money_source_transactions
* money_distributions
* money_distribution_lines

Authorized users with add_money permission can also manage distributions.

---

# Notifications

System-generated notifications.

Examples:

* Expense Updated
* Budget Updated
* Permission Granted
* Money Distributed

Database:

notifications

Users:

* See own notifications only

Owner:

* Receives expense update notifications

---

# Activity Logs

Every important action is recorded.

Examples:

* Expense Created
* Expense Updated
* Budget Updated
* Permission Granted
* Permission Revoked
* Money Distributed

